products.name: Taboule Salad
products.description: Taboule salad or Tabbouleh is a simple Mediterranean salad of very finely chopped vegetables, lots of fresh parsley and bulgur wheat, all tossed with lime juice and olive oil. Grab my tips and watch the video for how to make tabouli below. Tabouli is likely the topmost famed Mediterranean/Middle Eastern salad there is..

products.name: Greek Salad

details.name: Vegan Diet
details.description: A well-balanced diet that provides all the essential nutrients in the right amount is important for maintaining a healthy body and preventing chronic diseases.

details.name: Atkins Diet
details.description: Each type of diet has its own set of guidelines and restrictions on what foods to eat and what to avoid. The purpose of following a diet can vary from individual to individual, such as to improve overall health, to manage specific medical conditions, to lose weight, or to gain weight.

details.name: Whole30 Diet
details.description: A diet is a particular selection of food that a person chooses to eat regularly for maintaining good health or for weight loss purposes. There are various types of diets, including but not limited to, ketogenic diet, Mediterranean diet, vegetarian diet, vegan diet, low-carb diet, low-fat diet, and paleo diet.

details.name: Keto Diet
details.description: The keto diet is a high-fat, low-carb diet that aims to help you lose weight by putting your body in a state of ketosis. This means that your body is burning fat for fuel instead of carbs. The diet typically consists of 70-75% fat, 20-25% protein, and 5-10% carbs.

details.name: Paleo Diet
details.breakfast: Sweet Potato Hash with Fried Eggs
details.lunch: Grilled Chicken Salad with Avocado Dressing
details.description: The paleo diet is a way of eating that mimics the diets of our hunter-gatherer ancestors. It is based on the premise that our bodies are designed to eat the foods that were available to us before the advent of agriculture. This means that the diet typically consists of lean meats, fish, fruits, vegetables, nuts, and seeds.

details.name: Mediterranean Diet
details.breakfast: Greek Yogurt with Berries and Granola
details.dinner: Grilled Fish with Lemon and Herbs
details.description: The Mediterranean diet is based on the traditional diets of countries bordering the Mediterranean Sea. It emphasizes whole, minimally processed foods, including fruits, vegetables, whole grains, fish, and olive oil. The diet also includes moderate amounts of dairy and red wine, and limited amounts of red meat.

details.name: Ketogenic Diet
details.description: Ketogenic diet is a high-fat, low-carbohydrate diet that has been shown to help people lose weight. The idea behind the diet is to get your body into a state of ketosis, where it is burning fat for fuel instead of carbohydrates.

details.name: Flexitarian Diet
details.breakfast: Greek yogurt with fruit and honey
details.description: The Flexitarian Diet is a way of eating that is based on the traditional cuisine of countries bordering the Flexitarian Sea. The diet is characterized by an emphasis on plant-based foods, such as fruits, vegetables, whole grains, legumes, nuts, and seeds, with a moderate consumption of fish, seafood, poultry, and dairy products. It also includes a limited intake of red meat and sweets.
